	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99408874999048>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=99408874999048>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99408874999048>RE: twisting songs</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99408874999048#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Jul 2nd 11:45 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=48387><span id=Sage>Botten</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>32 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>To further illustrate let me give you an example:<br><br>To twist 3 song (memmed onto the "spell/song" bar) do the following:<br><br>Basic twisting:<br>---------------<br>1) Click on the first song. All "spells/songs" will go gray while you are singing. Watch your text area. Soon you will see a message saying that the song is doing its work.<br>2) When you see the message immediately click on the first song again. This stops you from singing that song. However the effect of the song will last a bit. All your "spells/songs" should now be available (ungrayed) again.<br>3) Click on the second song you want to sing. Again, all your "spells/songs" will go gray. Watch your text area again. When you see a message saying that the song has taken effect you now will have 2 effects in place.<br>4) When you see the message immediately click on the second song to turn it off.<br>5) Click on the third song you want to sing. When it starts you will have the effects from 3 songs working for you at once.<br>6) Stop the third song and start the first again. Keep going in a circle and the three songs should be playing continuously.<br><br>This all depends on how quick you are starting and stopping your singing, of course. If you start a song and let it play for 10 seconds before you stop it and start another the effect of the others will have faded. Also, if you start a song and stop it before the effect begins, you gain nothing. Timing is everything.<br><br>Advanced twisting:<br>------------------<br>The method is the same as that mentioned above, but some find it easier to place your songs in your "action boxes" so that you can start and stop singing with the keyboard instead of using the mouse.<br>Drag your songs from the "spell/song" bar into boxes 1 and 2 for example (the top two). Then you can twist by typing 11 22 11 22 etc.. Add a third song to box 3 and you can twist all three by typing 11 22 33 11 22 33 etc...<br><br>I hope this helps.<br><br>Ok everybody, Lets do the twist!<br><br>/emote starts dancing.<br><br>Lilt,&nbsp;&nbsp; Bard    - Saryrn<br>Enwyn,  Monk    - Saryrn<br>Galius, Paladin - Saryrn<br>Botten, Cleric  - Saryrn</p>&nbsp;<br>Botten Baggens<br>6 Earthen Lane<br>Rivervale<br>Saryrn<br><br>Galius Dalmatius<br>N. Freeport<br>Saryrn</td></td></tr>
