	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=99385604918821>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99385604918821>RE: twisting songs</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=99385604918821#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jun 29th 7:07 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=70506><span id= >Warbler</span></a><br><span id=notbold>12 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Twisting can begin at lvl 2 or 3, it isn't a skill suchas percussion instruments.&nbsp;&nbsp;the max # of songs being twisted is usually 3, although some expert twisters say they can do 5.  I think this would be impossible, but hey, who am I?<br>To twist, 1st start a song.  When you see the text saying hte song is in effect, turn it off and start hte next one.  When you see the text that it has started, begin the 3rd song, by the time th 3rd song has started, the 1st one should almost be ending, and it all goes in a big circle.   <br><br>However, some songs don't last long enough to be twisted- Clarity and mana songs are good exaples.  You can usually get around this by devoting two "slots" to the short songs, and using only 1 other song.  <br><br>Warbler<br>Bard of the 5th Song<br>Bristlebane Server</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
